  "prompt": "What is meant by digital transactions in India?",
  "response": "Digital transactions in India refer to financial transactions conducted electronically without the use of physical cash. Some key aspects include:\n\n1. Types of Digital Transactions:\n- Online banking transfers\n- Mobile banking\n- UPI (Unified Payments Interface)\n- Digital wallets\n- Credit/debit card payments\n- NEFT/RTGS transfers\n- IMPS (Immediate Payment Service)\n- QR code-based payments\n\n2. Government Initiatives:\n- Demonetization in 2016 promoted digital transactions\n- Digital India campaign\n- BHIM (Bharat Interface for Money) app\n- Promotion of cashless economy\n\n3. Key Benefits:\n- Convenience\n- Reduced transaction costs\n- Increased transparency\n- Easier tracking of financial transactions\n- Reduced cash handling risks\n\n4. Major Platforms:\n- Paytm\n- Google Pay\n- PhonePe\n- Amazon Pay\n- BHIM app\n\n5. Regulatory Framework:\n- Regulated by RBI\n- Strict security protocols\n- Data protection measures\n\nDigital transactions have significantly transformed India's financial landscape, promoting financial inclusion and modernizing the payment ecosystem.",
